Help Type: command
Command: wikigraph <uri>

URI Command

Target:
  {{ uri }}

{% if target.name == "archive-scope" %}
URI type:
  Archive scope

Default behavior:
  - `wikigraph {{ uri }}` enumerates archive-level objects.
  - `wikigraph {{ uri }} --query <query>` applies keyword retrieval across archive scopes.

Use when:
  - You need the archive entry point before narrowing to chapters, chunks, entities, triples, source, or summaries.
{% elif target.name == "chapter-collection-scope" %}
URI type:
  Chapter collection scope

Default behavior:
  - `wikigraph {{ uri }}` enumerates chapters.
  - `wikigraph {{ uri }} --query <query>` applies keyword retrieval to chapter objects.

Use when:
  - You need chapter ids, chapter readiness, or a starting point for chapter-scoped retrieval.
{% elif target.name == "chapter-scope" %}
URI type:
  Chapter scope

Default behavior:
  - `wikigraph {{ uri }}` enumerates objects inside this chapter.
  - `wikigraph {{ uri }} --query <query>` applies keyword retrieval inside this chapter.

Use when:
  - You already selected a chapter and want local source, summary, chunk, entity, or triple objects.
{% elif target.name == "chunk-scope" %}
URI type:
  Chunk scope

Default behavior:
  - `wikigraph {{ uri }}` enumerates Reading Graph chunks.
  - `wikigraph {{ uri }} --query <query>` applies keyword retrieval to chunks in this scope.

Use when:
  - You need candidate Reading Graph chunks before selecting a concrete chunk URI.
{% elif target.name == "entity-scope" %}
URI type:
  Entity scope

Default behavior:
  - `wikigraph {{ uri }}` enumerates Knowledge Graph entities.
  - `wikigraph {{ uri }} --query <query>` applies keyword retrieval to entities in this scope.

Use when:
  - You need candidate entities before selecting a concrete entity URI.
{% elif target.name == "triple-scope" %}
URI type:
  Triple scope

Default behavior:
  - `wikigraph {{ uri }}` enumerates Knowledge Graph triples matching this scope or pattern.
  - `wikigraph {{ uri }} --query <query>` applies keyword retrieval to triples in this scope.

Use when:
  - You need relation candidates or a triple pattern such as `_` placeholders.
{% elif target.name == "chapter-source-object" %}
URI type:
  Chapter source object

Default behavior:
  - `wikigraph {{ uri }}` reads source text.
  - Source range fragments such as `#4..8` read sentence numbers 4 through 8, inclusive.
  - Range sentence numbers are 1-based. `#1` is the first sentence; `#1..2` is the first two sentences.
  - Whole source reads are plain text streams and do not support `--json`; source range fragments are structured range objects and support `--json`.

Use when:
  - You need continuous original wording from a selected chapter.
{% elif target.name == "chapter-summary-object" or target.name == "summary-object" %}
URI type:
  Summary object

Default behavior:
  - `wikigraph {{ uri }}` reads summary text.
  - Summary range fragments such as `#4..8` read sentence numbers 4 through 8, inclusive.
  - Range sentence numbers are 1-based. `#1` is the first sentence; `#1..2` is the first two sentences.
  - Whole summary reads are plain text streams and do not support `--json`; summary range fragments are structured range objects and support `--json`.

Use when:
  - You need compact readable prose before tracing source evidence.
{% elif target.name == "chapter-title-object" %}
URI type:
  Chapter title object

Default behavior:
  - `wikigraph {{ uri }}` reads the chapter title.

Use when:
  - You need the current title or want to set or clear it.
{% elif target.name == "chapter-tree-object" %}
URI type:
  Chapter tree object

Default behavior:
  - `wikigraph {{ uri }}` reads the table-of-contents tree.

Use when:
  - You need the global chapter structure before choosing scopes.
{% elif target.name == "chapter-state-object" %}
URI type:
  Chapter state object

Default behavior:
  - `wikigraph {{ uri }}` reads generated artifact readiness.

Use when:
  - You need to know whether source, Reading Graph, Reading Summary, or Knowledge Graph data exists for a chapter.
{% elif target.name == "chunk-object" %}
URI type:
  Chunk object

Default behavior:
  - `wikigraph {{ uri }}` reads one Reading Graph chunk.

Use when:
  - You selected a chunk and need to read, expand, verify, or pack it.
{% elif target.name == "entity-object" %}
URI type:
  Entity object

Default behavior:
  - `wikigraph {{ uri }}` reads one Knowledge Graph entity.

Use when:
  - You selected an entity and need related triples, source evidence, or packed context.
{% elif target.name == "entity-wikipage-object" %}
URI type:
  Entity wikipage object

Default behavior:
  - `wikigraph {{ uri }}` reads mapped Wikipedia page data for the entity.

Use when:
  - You need canonical mapped pages before considering external web lookup.
{% elif target.name == "triple-object" %}
URI type:
  Triple object

Default behavior:
  - `wikigraph {{ uri }}` reads one Knowledge Graph relation.

Use when:
  - You selected a concrete subject, predicate, and object relation.
{% elif target.name == "cover-object" %}
URI type:
  Cover object

Default behavior:
  - `wikigraph {{ uri }}` writes raw cover bytes to stdout.

Use when:
  - You need to redirect or pipe the cover resource.
{% elif target.name == "index-object" %}
URI type:
  Index object

Default behavior:
  - `wikigraph {{ uri }}` reads the archive FTS index policy.

Use when:
  - You need to inspect, enable, disable, embed, or externalize searchable FTS index support.
{% elif target.name == "job-collection-scope" %}
URI type:
  Local job collection scope

Default behavior:
  - `wikigraph {{ uri }}` shows local generation jobs.

Use when:
  - You need to inspect, add, or clean local generation jobs.
{% elif target.name == "job-object" %}
URI type:
  Local job object

Default behavior:
  - `wikigraph {{ uri }}` reads local job status.

Use when:
  - You need job status, progress, or lifecycle control.
{% elif target.name == "job-target-object" %}
URI type:
  Local job target object

Default behavior:
  - `wikigraph {{ uri }}` is not a retrieval shortcut. Use `set`.

Use when:
  - You need to change an active job target.
{% elif target.name == "local-config-section" %}
URI type:
  Local config section

Default behavior:
  - `wikigraph {{ uri }}` reads the section.

Use when:
  - You need to read, replace, edit, clear, or test local configuration.
{% if "/wikispine" in uri %}

WikiSpine runtime guide:
  https://raw.githubusercontent.com/oomol-lab/wiki-graph/refs/heads/main/docs/wikispine-runtime.md
{% endif %}
{% endif %}

Predicate commands:
{% if target.predicates.length %}
{% for predicate in target.predicates %}
{% if predicate == "add" %}
  - add: create a child object or local job. Help: wikigraph {{ uri }} add --help
{% elif predicate == "boost" %}
  - boost: move a waiting job forward. Help: wikigraph {{ uri }} boost --help
{% elif predicate == "cancel" %}
  - cancel: cancel a local job. Help: wikigraph {{ uri }} cancel --help
{% elif predicate == "clean" %}
  - clean: remove completed local jobs. Help: wikigraph {{ uri }} clean --help
{% elif predicate == "clear" %}
  - clear: clear a writable resource or config section. Help: wikigraph {{ uri }} clear --help
{% elif predicate == "create" %}
  - create: create the archive; use `--replace` only when discarding an existing archive. Help: wikigraph {{ uri }} create --help
{% elif predicate == "delete" %}
  - delete: delete a config key. Help: wikigraph {{ uri }} delete --help
{% elif predicate == "disable" %}
  - disable: disable searchable index support and remove index materialization. Help: wikigraph {{ uri }} disable --help
{% elif predicate == "embed" %}
  - embed: use archive-embedded searchable index storage. Help: wikigraph {{ uri }} embed --help
{% elif predicate == "enable" %}
  - enable: enable searchable index support and bring it to current. Help: wikigraph {{ uri }} enable --help
{% elif predicate == "evidence" %}
  - evidence: trace this object to source-backed evidence; supports `--reverse` without `--query`. Help: wikigraph {{ uri }} evidence --help
{% elif predicate == "export" %}
  - export: export an archive projection. Help: wikigraph {{ uri }} export --help
{% elif predicate == "external" %}
  - external: use local-cache searchable index storage. Help: wikigraph {{ uri }} external --help
{% elif predicate == "inspect" %}
  - inspect: inspect archive readiness. Help: wikigraph {{ uri }} inspect --help
{% elif predicate == "move" %}
  - move: move a chapter in the tree. Help: wikigraph {{ uri }} move --help
{% elif predicate == "pack" %}
  - pack: assemble bounded context around this object. Help: wikigraph {{ uri }} pack --help
{% elif predicate == "pause" %}
  - pause: pause a local job. Help: wikigraph {{ uri }} pause --help
{% elif predicate == "put" %}
  - put: set one config key. Help: wikigraph {{ uri }} put --help
{% elif predicate == "related" %}
  - related: expand from this object to nearby objects; supports `--reverse` without `--query`. Help: wikigraph {{ uri }} related --help
{% elif predicate == "remove" %}
  - remove: remove a chapter. Help: wikigraph {{ uri }} remove --help
{% elif predicate == "reset" %}
  - reset: delete later-stage chapter artifacts. Help: wikigraph {{ uri }} reset --help
{% elif predicate == "resume" %}
  - resume: resume a local job. Help: wikigraph {{ uri }} resume --help
{% elif predicate == "set" %}
  - set: modify this writable target. Help: wikigraph {{ uri }} set --help
{% elif predicate == "test" %}
  - test: test local config connectivity. Help: wikigraph {{ uri }} test --help
{% elif predicate == "watch" %}
  - watch: follow local job progress. Help: wikigraph {{ uri }} watch --help
{% endif %}
{% endfor %}
{% else %}
  This URI has no additional predicate commands. Use the naked URI command shown above.
{% endif %}
